problemplot = df %>%
  group_by(problem) %>%
  summarise(count = n()) %>%
  ggplot(aes(x = reorder(problem,(-count)), y = count)) +
  geom_bar(stat = 'identity') +
  theme_economist() +
  xlab('') +
  ylab('') +
  ggtitle('Reasons for Traffic Stop')

citationplot = df %>%

  ylab('') +
  ggtitle('Citation Issued')

#Now let's examine the policing style of each precint.
# Even though blacks make up the majority of traffic stops, the majority come from precinct 4
blacktotal = df %>%
  group_by(policePrecinct) %>%
  summarise(perc = sum(race == 'Black', na.rm=T) / n())

blacktotalplot = 
  ggplot(blacktotal, aes(y = perc, x=policePrecinct)) +
  geom_bar(stat='identity') +
  scale_y_continuous(labels= scales::percent) +
  theme_economist() +
  ylab('') +
  xlab('Precinct') +
  ggtitle('Proportion of Stops: Black')

#While running proportion tests, it became apparent to me that the large numbers of observations will make each test significant. 
#Precinct 1-- 63% of the time, pulls over Blacks for suspicious activity; whites about 50%; 30% of all stops are blacks, 20% whites
#precinct 2-- 25% suspicious activity blacks; 25% whites; 20% blacks, 30% whites
#precinct 3-- 60% suspicious activity blacks, 50% whites; 23% stops are blacks, 12% whites
#precinct 4-- 26% suspitcious activity blacks; 27% whites; 50% stops black, 10% whites

byday = df %>%
  group_by(date=floor_date(date, '1 day')) %>%
  summarise(count = length(date))
  
byday %>%  
  ggplot(aes(x=date, y=count)) +
  geom_line() 


byday = byday %>%
  dplyr::mutate(weeklyavg = zoo::rollmean(count, k=7, fill=NA))
byday %>%
  pivot_longer(names_to = 'rolling_mean_key',
                      values_to = 'rolling_mean_value',
                      cols = c(weeklyavg,
                      count)) %>%
  ggplot(aes(x=date,
                      y=rolling_mean_value,
                      color = rolling_mean_key)) +
  geom_line() +
  labs(title='Weekly Rolling Average of Traffic Stops',
                y='Traffic Stops',
                x='Date',
                color='Metric',) +
  scale_x_datetime(breaks=date_breaks('1 month'), date_labels = '%m %Y')

map1 = df%>%filter(policePrecinct == '4',
                   race %in% c('Black', 'White'))

colorFactor_races = colorFactor(
  palette = c('blue', 'darkorange'),
  levels = c('Black','White'))

leaflet(sample_n(map1, 300)) %>%
  addProviderTiles(provider = 'Stamen') %>%
  addCircles(
    color = ~colorFactor_races(map1$race),
    opacity = 1,
    fillOpacity = 1
  ) %>%
  addLegend(
    pal = colorFactor_races,
    values = c('Black', 'White'),
    title = 'Stops by Race',
    position = 'topleft',
    opacity=1
  )
